<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Philippines and Malaysia (Borneo: Sabah).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="note o">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Note O.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<bibRefCitation author="Vidal, S" journalOrPublisher="Perez, Manila" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/51599page/6/mode/1up" refId="B44" refString="Vidal, S, 1886. Revision de Plantas Vasculares Filipinas. M. Perez, Manila, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/51599page/6/mode/1up" title="Revision de Plantas Vasculares Filipinas. M." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/51599page/6/mode/1up" year="1886">Vidal (1886)</bibRefCitation>
designated two collections as the type when he described 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1821" authorityName="Vidal" authorityYear="1886" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Eriobotrya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriobotrya philippinensis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="philippinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Eriobotrya philippinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his work &quot;Revision de Plantas Vasculares Filipinas&quot;, therefore, they are syntypes (Art. 9.6: 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" refId="B42" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, D, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, 2018. International code of nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International code of nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). We herein select the flowering specimen (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. Vidal 1350</emphasis>
) as a candidate for the lectotype, however, two duplicates of this collection were located in herbaria K and MA. We must narrow the lectotype to a single sheet. In the 1870s Vidal took up posts in the forestry service of the Philippines, however, in 1883 he was back in Europe and visited the herbaria there including K (
<bibRefCitation author="Vidal, S" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" refId="B43" refString="Vidal, S, 1885. Phanerogamae Cumingianae Philippinarum: o, Indice Numerico y Catalogo Sistematico de las Plantas Fanerogamas Coleccionadas en Filipinas. M. Perez Hijo, 217 pp." title="Phanerogamae Cumingianae Philippinarum: o, Indice Numerico y Catalogo Sistematico de las Plantas Fanerogamas Coleccionadas en Filipinas. M. Perez Hijo, 217 pp." year="1885">Vidal 1885</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, we herein designate the sheet of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. Vidal 1350</emphasis>
in K (barcode K000758204) as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="note p">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Note P.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.17674" author="Merrill, ED" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Bureau of Science Government Laboratories" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="5 - 47" refId="B27" refString="Merrill, ED, 1904. New or noteworthy Philippine plants, II. Publications of the Bureau of Science Government Laboratories 17: 5 - 47, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.17674" title="New or noteworthy Philippine plants, II." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.17674" volume="17" year="1904">Merrill (1904)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merr" authorityYear="1904" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Photinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Photinia luzonensis" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luzonensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Photinia luzonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and mentioned two collections (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">E.D. Merrill 3223 &amp; 3714</emphasis>
) in the protologue, and thus they are syntypes (Art. 9.6: 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" refId="B42" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, D, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, 2018. International code of nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International code of nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Kalkman, C" journalOrPublisher="Blumea" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" pagination="413 - 442" publicationUrl="https://www.repository.naturalis.nl/document/564949" refId="B14" refString="Kalkman, C, 1973. The Malesian species of the subfamily Maloideae. Blumea 21: 413 - 442, https://www.repository.naturalis.nl/document/564949" title="The Malesian species of the subfamily Maloideae." url="https://www.repository.naturalis.nl/document/564949" volume="21" year="1973">Kalkman (1973)</bibRefCitation>
wrote as &quot;Type: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Merrill 3223</emphasis>
(K, iso); paratype: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Merrill 3714</emphasis>
(BM, K)&quot;, which means that he designated 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Merrill 3223</emphasis>
as the lectotype [first-step]. We located two duplicates in herbaria NY and K, respectively, and thus it is necessary to narrow the lectotype to one single specimen. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/104137page/7/mode/1up" refId="B37" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1981. Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Volume III: Lh-O. Regnum Vegetabile 105. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht &amp; dr. W. Junk b.v., Publisher, The Hague. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/104137page/7/mode/1up" title="Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Volume III: Lh-O. Regnum Vegetabile 105. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht &amp; dr. W. Junk b. v., Publisher, The Hague." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/104137page/7/mode/1up" year="1981">Stafleu and Cowan (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Merrill’s">Merrill's</normalizedToken>
type and material are deposited in A, FH, NY, PNH, and UC. We, therefore, designate the sheet in NY (barcode 00436125) as the lectotype [second-step].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
